[metadata]
Name:Spirit Link lifelink fires on combat damage to a creature (mtg-m43mc)
Goal:Win
Turns:2
Difficulty:Easy
Description:Regression for mtg-m43mc / mtg-r9po1. A creature enchanted with Spirit Link is BLOCKED, so it deals combat damage only to a creature (the blocker), never to a player. Spirit Link's "whenever enchanted creature deals damage, you gain that much life" trigger must still fire (CR 510.2 / 119.3): the controller gains life equal to the combat damage dealt to the blocker. Board: P0 has a 3/3 Hill Giant enchanted with Spirit Link; P1 has a 0/8 Wall of Stone blocker that survives, so the Hill Giant deals 3 to the Wall and 0 to any player. P0 must gain 3 life. The e2e test attaches Spirit Link and declares the block explicitly (puzzle attachment is not yet supported by the loader).

